            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "IDK if the message grid behavior regarding this was ever motivated or just happens to work that way (`'cmdheight' = 0` is still marked as experimental).\n\nOn the message grid, the cmdline is drawn over the statusline, but when the cmdline becomes so long that it doesn't fit on a single line the msgsep separator suddenly appears (which doesn't happen with Vim so it looks like an implementation detail of the message grid implementation of our cmdline).\n\nBoth of these behaviors appear more surprising to me than simply using the statusline as the cmdline separator (if it exists, depending on 'laststatus'). Vim works that way too.",
